{"actual":"All checked identifiers agreed; ./nexus verify and ./nexus audit-check both reported PASS.","audit_id":"AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND","audit_layer":"ARCHIVE","audit_phase":"BLIND","auditor":{"model_family":"Anthropic","model_name":"claude-sonnet-5","provider":"Anthropic","session_label":"second-account"},"claim":"Under untampered conditions the four-way binding holds: baseline-001 dereferences to TARGET.json.target_commit, the tag object equals TARGET.json.target_ref_object, the snapshot's embedded _nexus/SNAPSHOT_METADATA.json source_commit equals target_commit, and the archive SHA-256 equals TARGET.json.target_archive_sha256 and the route pack digest.","classification":"OBSERVATION","confidence":"HIGH","created_at":"2026-07-12T23:30:00Z","evidence_refs":["sha256sum of target archive matched TARGET.json.target_archive_sha256","git rev-parse baseline-001 == 5e5331a61664335932d855160a4b26c4c3bae2a8 (target_ref_object)","git rev-parse baseline-001^0 == 7a8068fc6088b81cc9a7c94b49dc77e0abe592d8 (target_commit)","extracted _nexus/SNAPSHOT_METADATA.json source_commit == 7a8068fc6088b81cc9a7c94b49dc77e0abe592d8","./nexus audit-check --audit-id AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND returned status PASS"],"exact_location":["operations/audits/AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND/TARGET.json","operations/audits/AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND/target/NEXUS_LAB_R001_BASELINE_001.zip","operations/audits/AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND/EXTERNAL_WITNESS_ARCHITECTURE.md"],"expected":"All independently checked identifiers agree with TARGET.json as required by EXTERNAL_WITNESS_ARCHITECTURE.md.","files_not_seen":[],"files_seen":["operations/audits/AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND/TARGET.json","operations/audits/AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND/target/NEXUS_LAB_R001_BASELINE_001.zip","operations/audits/AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND/target/NEXUS_LAB_R001_BASELINE_001.zip.sha256","snapshots/canonical/NEXUS_LAB_R001_BASELINE_001.zip"],"limitations":["This confirms the binding holds for the current, untampered worktree only; it does not by itself prove the binding is enforced against adversarial edits (see AUDOBS-0003)."],"observation_id":"AUDOBS-R002-CLAUDE-0001","previous_record_hash":"","recommended_future_change":"","record_hash":"","reproduction":["sha256sum operations/audits/AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND/target/NEXUS_LAB_R001_BASELINE_001.zip","git rev-parse baseline-001 && git rev-parse baseline-001^0","unzip -p ... _nexus/SNAPSHOT_METADATA.json","./nexus audit-check --audit-id AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND"],"schema":"nexus.audit-observation/v1","severity":"INFO","status_authority":"NONE","suggested_next_test":"","target_archive_sha256":"33d3fb549d49e1ad02ac2b2880b5ab4336a6dc29a7142d3e33e4ec2694ad8603","target_commit":"7a8068fc6088b81cc9a7c94b49dc77e0abe592d8"}
{"actual":"Rejected with NexusError as expected. Exit code 2.","audit_id":"AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND","audit_layer":"APPARATUS","audit_phase":"BLIND","auditor":{"model_family":"Anthropic","model_name":"claude-sonnet-5","provider":"Anthropic","session_label":"second-account"},"claim":"./nexus audit-check correctly detects raw archive-byte substitution when the archive no longer matches TARGET.json.target_archive_sha256.","classification":"OBSERVATION","confidence":"HIGH","created_at":"2026-07-12T23:30:00Z","evidence_refs":["In an isolated git clone (not the source repository), appending one byte to the target archive and running ./nexus audit-check produced: NEXUS ERROR: Snapshot digest mismatch: expected 33d3fb..., got b034b3..."],"exact_location":["system/nexus_lab/snapshot.py:verify_snapshot","system/nexus_lab/audit.py:check_audit"],"expected":"Substitution is detected and rejected per EXTERNAL_WITNESS_ARCHITECTURE.md.","files_not_seen":[],"files_seen":["system/nexus_lab/snapshot.py","system/nexus_lab/audit.py"],"limitations":["Tested only in an isolated temporary clone; the source repository was never modified."],"observation_id":"AUDOBS-R002-CLAUDE-0002","previous_record_hash":"","recommended_future_change":"","record_hash":"","reproduction":["git clone <repo> /tmp/clone","append a byte to operations/audits/AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND/target/NEXUS_LAB_R001_BASELINE_001.zip in the clone","./nexus --root /tmp/clone audit-check --audit-id AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND"],"schema":"nexus.audit-observation/v1","severity":"INFO","status_authority":"NONE","suggested_next_test":"","target_archive_sha256":"33d3fb549d49e1ad02ac2b2880b5ab4336a6dc29a7142d3e33e4ec2694ad8603","target_commit":"7a8068fc6088b81cc9a7c94b49dc77e0abe592d8"}
{"actual":"audit-check trusts TARGET.json's declared digest as ground truth and only cross-checks the archive against that same, co-located, mutable file; it does not re-derive the archive from the immutable git tree at target_commit, nor does it require or check a clean git worktree.","audit_id":"AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND","audit_layer":"APPARATUS","audit_phase":"BLIND","auditor":{"model_family":"Anthropic","model_name":"claude-sonnet-5","provider":"Anthropic","session_label":"second-account"},"claim":"If an actor with working-tree write access substitutes the target archive AND edits TARGET.json's target_archive_sha256 in the same audit directory to match the forged bytes, ./nexus audit-check reports PASS. The tool has no anchor for the audit directory's own declared digest that is independent of the audit directory itself, and audit-check does not check git worktree cleanliness before trusting on-disk files.","classification":"SUSPECTED_DEFECT","confidence":"HIGH","created_at":"2026-07-12T23:30:00Z","evidence_refs":["In an isolated clone, appending a byte to the archive and rewriting TARGET.json.target_archive_sha256 to the newly forged digest caused ./nexus audit-check to print target_sha256=1752cac2... and status: PASS, even though the archive no longer matches the originally frozen bytes.","ensure_clean_worktree() exists in util.py and is used by github_bootstrap, but check_audit()/verify_repository() never call it."],"exact_location":["system/nexus_lab/audit.py:check_audit","system/nexus_lab/audit.py:build_audit_pack"],"expected":"EXTERNAL_WITNESS_ARCHITECTURE.md states digest mismatch is a failure condition, implying the binding is independently verifiable.","files_not_seen":[],"files_seen":["system/nexus_lab/audit.py","system/nexus_lab/util.py"],"limitations":["Tested only in an isolated temporary clone; the source repository was never modified.","In practice this requires local write access to tracked files without committing, or a malicious/careless commit; CI runs on a fresh checkout, so this specific vector is likely CI-mitigated but that mitigation is not enforced by the tool itself.","Did not test whether ./nexus doctor's git_repository check (which does report DIRTY) is wired into any operator workflow that would catch this before audit-check is trusted."],"observation_id":"AUDOBS-R002-CLAUDE-0003","previous_record_hash":"","recommended_future_change":"Add an independent recomputation step: rebuild the payload manifest from the live git tree at target_commit and compare it to the archive's embedded payload manifest, instead of only comparing against a digest declared in a co-located, git-tracked-but-editable JSON file.","record_hash":"","reproduction":["git clone <repo> /tmp/clone","append a byte to the target archive in the clone","recompute its sha256 and overwrite TARGET.json.target_archive_sha256 with that value","./nexus --root /tmp/clone audit-check --audit-id AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND","observe status: PASS despite the archive bytes differing from the pristine snapshot"],"schema":"nexus.audit-observation/v1","severity":"MEDIUM","status_authority":"NONE","suggested_next_test":"Have check_audit() (or verify_repository()) refuse to run, or downgrade its status, when git status --short is non-empty for the audit directory; alternatively, have it re-derive the snapshot from git ls-tree at target_commit and compare bytes directly rather than trusting TARGET.json's declared digest alone.","target_archive_sha256":"33d3fb549d49e1ad02ac2b2880b5ab4336a6dc29a7142d3e33e4ec2694ad8603","target_commit":"7a8068fc6088b81cc9a7c94b49dc77e0abe592d8"}
{"actual":"Rejected with NexusError as expected.","audit_id":"AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND","audit_layer":"APPARATUS","audit_phase":"BLIND","auditor":{"model_family":"Anthropic","model_name":"claude-sonnet-5","provider":"Anthropic","session_label":"second-account"},"claim":"./nexus audit-check correctly detects tag movement (retargeting baseline-001 to a different commit).","classification":"OBSERVATION","confidence":"HIGH","created_at":"2026-07-12T23:30:00Z","evidence_refs":["In an isolated clone, running `git tag -f baseline-001 HEAD` (HEAD != target_commit) then ./nexus audit-check produced: NEXUS ERROR: Audit target_ref does not resolve to target_commit; the ref may have moved. Exit code 2."],"exact_location":["system/nexus_lab/audit.py:check_audit","system/nexus_lab/util.py:resolve_commit"],"expected":"Tag movement is a failure condition per EXTERNAL_WITNESS_ARCHITECTURE.md.","files_not_seen":[],"files_seen":["system/nexus_lab/audit.py"],"limitations":["Tested only in an isolated temporary clone; the source repository was never modified."],"observation_id":"AUDOBS-R002-CLAUDE-0004","previous_record_hash":"","recommended_future_change":"","record_hash":"","reproduction":["git clone <repo> /tmp/clone","git -C /tmp/clone tag -f baseline-001 HEAD","./nexus --root /tmp/clone audit-check --audit-id AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND"],"schema":"nexus.audit-observation/v1","severity":"INFO","status_authority":"NONE","suggested_next_test":"","target_archive_sha256":"33d3fb549d49e1ad02ac2b2880b5ab4336a6dc29a7142d3e33e4ec2694ad8603","target_commit":"7a8068fc6088b81cc9a7c94b49dc77e0abe592d8"}
{"actual":"Rejected with NexusError as expected, correctly distinguishing tag-object identity from commit identity.","audit_id":"AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND","audit_layer":"APPARATUS","audit_phase":"BLIND","auditor":{"model_family":"Anthropic","model_name":"claude-sonnet-5","provider":"Anthropic","session_label":"second-account"},"claim":"./nexus audit-check correctly detects annotated-tag object replacement even when the replacement tag still dereferences to the identical target commit.","classification":"OBSERVATION","confidence":"HIGH","created_at":"2026-07-12T23:30:00Z","evidence_refs":["In an isolated clone, deleting baseline-001 and recreating it as a new annotated tag object pointed at the same target commit (7a8068fc...) produced a new tag object hash (dc45901a...) differing from TARGET.json.target_ref_object (5e5331a6...). ./nexus audit-check then reported: NEXUS ERROR: Audit target_ref object does not match TARGET.json; the tag may have been replaced. Exit code 2."],"exact_location":["system/nexus_lab/audit.py:check_audit"],"expected":"Tag object replacement is a failure condition per EXTERNAL_WITNESS_ARCHITECTURE.md, distinct from tag movement.","files_not_seen":[],"files_seen":["system/nexus_lab/audit.py"],"limitations":["Tested only in an isolated temporary clone; the source repository was never modified."],"observation_id":"AUDOBS-R002-CLAUDE-0005","previous_record_hash":"","recommended_future_change":"","record_hash":"","reproduction":["git clone <repo> /tmp/clone","git -C /tmp/clone tag -d baseline-001","git -C /tmp/clone tag -a baseline-001 -m 'forged retag' 7a8068fc6088b81cc9a7c94b49dc77e0abe592d8","./nexus --root /tmp/clone audit-check --audit-id AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND"],"schema":"nexus.audit-observation/v1","severity":"INFO","status_authority":"NONE","suggested_next_test":"","target_archive_sha256":"33d3fb549d49e1ad02ac2b2880b5ab4336a6dc29a7142d3e33e4ec2694ad8603","target_commit":"7a8068fc6088b81cc9a7c94b49dc77e0abe592d8"}
